	<entry>
		<title>Eve of Evil (Part 4)</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://nightland.website/index.php/stories/night-land-stories/the-days-of-darkening/47-eve-of-evil/129-eve-of-evil-part-4"/>
		<published>2015-06-03T21:02:17+00:00</published>
		<updated>2015-06-03T21:02:17+00:00</updated>
		<id>https://nightland.website/index.php/stories/night-land-stories/the-days-of-darkening/47-eve-of-evil/129-eve-of-evil-part-4</id>
		<author>
			<name>Kate Coady</name>
		</author>
		<summary type="html">&lt;h3 class=&quot;story-teaser&quot;&gt;By &lt;a href=&quot;https://nightland.website/index.php/background/authors-and-artists/121-gregg-marchese&quot;&gt;Gregg Marchese&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;story-intro&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://nightland.website/index.php/stories/night-land-stories/the-days-of-darkening/128-eve-of-evil-part-3&quot;&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;story-thumb&quot; src=&quot;https://nightland.website/images/thumbs/coady-eve-of-evil-illo-thumb.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;An evil-looking creature resembling a sideways jellyfish, closing in on prey.&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;story-teaser&quot;&gt;With swirls through its dark substance, a tunnel formed through the grey fog. Its opening stood aligned with Darlai's path toward the Periblima. Deep within, she thought she could see a distant flash of iridescence. Unquestioning, giving her terror full sway, she bolted into the tunnel...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</summary>
		<content type="html">&lt;h3 class=&quot;story-teaser&quot;&gt;By &lt;a href=&quot;https://nightland.website/index.php/background/authors-and-artists/121-gregg-marchese&quot;&gt;Gregg Marchese&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;story-intro&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://nightland.website/index.php/stories/night-land-stories/the-days-of-darkening/128-eve-of-evil-part-3&quot;&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;story-thumb&quot; src=&quot;https://nightland.website/images/thumbs/coady-eve-of-evil-illo-thumb.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;An evil-looking creature resembling a sideways jellyfish, closing in on prey.&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;story-teaser&quot;&gt;With swirls through its dark substance, a tunnel formed through the grey fog. Its opening stood aligned with Darlai's path toward the Periblima. Deep within, she thought she could see a distant flash of iridescence. Unquestioning, giving her terror full sway, she bolted into the tunnel...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</content>
		<category term="Eve of Evil (Part 4)" />
