	<entry>
		<title>Red Twilight</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://nightland.website/index.php/stories/night-land-stories/the-days-of-darkening/3-red-twilight"/>
		<published>2015-04-19T18:40:48+00:00</published>
		<updated>2015-04-19T18:40:48+00:00</updated>
		<id>https://nightland.website/index.php/stories/night-land-stories/the-days-of-darkening/3-red-twilight</id>
		<author>
			<name>Kate Coady</name>
		</author>
		<summary type="html">&lt;h3 class=&quot;story-teaser&quot;&gt;By &lt;a href=&quot;https://nightland.website/index.php/about/authors-and-artists/40-keran-parizek&quot;&gt;Keran Parizek&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;story-intro&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://nightland.website/index.php/stories/night-land-stories/the-days-of-darkening/3-red-twilight&quot;&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;story-thumb&quot; src=&quot;https://nightland.website/images/thumbs/coady-red-twilight-cover-unlettered-thumb.JPG&quot; alt=&quot;A blonde woman, dressed in green and holding a blazing plasma staff weapon, standing on a road against a red sky in a rocky volcanic wilderness. There are bizarre plants behind her.&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;story-teaser&quot;&gt;&quot;There had been other occasions when she'd caught the echoes of an undersong within the aether; but not before tonight had its tones carried strongly enough for her to know that she had not imagined it.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</summary>
		<content type="html">&lt;h3 class=&quot;story-teaser&quot;&gt;By &lt;a href=&quot;https://nightland.website/index.php/about/authors-and-artists/40-keran-parizek&quot;&gt;Keran Parizek&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;story-intro&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://nightland.website/index.php/stories/night-land-stories/the-days-of-darkening/3-red-twilight&quot;&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;story-thumb&quot; src=&quot;https://nightland.website/images/thumbs/coady-red-twilight-cover-unlettered-thumb.JPG&quot; alt=&quot;A blonde woman, dressed in green and holding a blazing plasma staff weapon, standing on a road against a red sky in a rocky volcanic wilderness. There are bizarre plants behind her.&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;story-teaser&quot;&gt;&quot;There had been other occasions when she'd caught the echoes of an undersong within the aether; but not before tonight had its tones carried strongly enough for her to know that she had not imagined it.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</content>
